   <refnamediv>
       <refname>movblockboot</refname>
               <refpurpose>Moving-block bootstrap </refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
 
        <refsynopsisdiv>
               <title>CALLING SEQUENCE</title>
               <synopsis>﻿ [ovb,selb,k,re]=movblockboot(T,l,B)</synopsis>
        </refsynopsisdiv>
 
        <refsection>
           <title>PARAMETERS</title>
           <variablelist>
           <varlistentry>
 
           <term>Input</term>
 
 
<listitem><para>*  <term> T </term> =    sample size</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> l </term> =    block length</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term> B </term> =    number of bootstrap replications</para></listitem>
 
 
<listitem><para>&#160;</para></listitem>
 
           </varlistentry>
 
          <varlistentry>
 
          <term>Output</term>
 
 
<listitem><para>*  <term>  ovb </term> =    (l x T/l) matrix that decomposes the initial sample into l overlapping blocks</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term>  selb </term> =    (T/l x B) matrix that randomly selects the overlapping blocks</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term>  k </term> =    number of blocks</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>*  <term>  re </term> =    size of the last block if T/l not an integer</para></listitem>
 
 
          </varlistentry>
          </variablelist>
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
In a moving-block bootstrap, gives the matrix that decomposes the initial sample into overlapping block and the matrix that randomly selects them.
        </refsection>
 
        <refsection>
               <title>AUTHOR</title>
Emmanuel Michaux 2012
        </refsection>
</refentry>
